see:

 - https://github.com/python/typing/issues/213

 1. To get rid of `error: Signature of &quot;x&quot; incompatible with supertype &quot;Fooish&quot;` you can annotate `x: typing.Any`.
 2. To make `Fooish` really abstract some tricks are needed to resolve metaclass conflict. I took a recipe from [this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/a/13661237/9609843):

```
class MyABCMeta(MyMeta, abc.ABCMeta):
